This paper is about automated mechanism design (AMD) in the domain of double auctions, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also describes an evolutionary search method, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the approach evaluates auction mechanisms using the framework of the TAC Market Design Game, which involves learning from data (cs.LG - Learning). The paper also mentions reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA - Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper discusses the economic properties of the auction mechanisms, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
